Concept:
Shape determines the dimensions of an array.
Reshape changes the shape without altering data.
Syntax:
# Checking shape
print(arr.shape)

# Reshaping
reshaped = arr.reshape(2, 3)
Examples:
arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])

# Reshaping
matrix = arr.reshape(2, 3)
print(matrix)
  
Questions:
Reshape a 1D array of size 12 into a 3x4 array.
Check the shape of a given 2D array.
